An account satisfies ¬ß 1005.2(b)(3)(i)(D) if its primary function is to provide general transaction capability, even if an individual consumer does not in fact use it to conduct multiple transactions. An account whose primary function is other than to conduct transactions with multiple, unaffiliated merchants for goods or services, or at automated teller machines, or to conduct person-to-person transfers, does not satisfy ¬ß 1005.2(b)(3)(i)(D). 9.  Redeemable upon presentation at multiple, unaffiliated merchants. For guidance, see comments 20(a)(3)--1 and --2.

10.  Person-to-person transfers. A prepaid account whose primary function is to conduct person-to-person transfers is an account that allows a consumer to send funds by electronic fund transfer to another consumer or business. An account may qualify as a prepaid account if its primary function is person-to-person transfers even if it is neither redeemable upon presentation at multiple, unaffiliated merchants for goods or services, nor usable at automated teller machines. A transaction involving a store gift card would not be a person-to-person transfer if it could only be used to make payments to the merchant or affiliated group of merchants on whose behalf the card was issued.

What are the benefits?
‚ú?Secure payments 
‚ú?1‚Ç?charged per transfer when depositing on advcash. No additional fees applied by Binance.

üî∏To get started:üî∏
First create your account by going to their website (Registration is free): https://wallet.advcash.com/register
You will then need to do your identity verification (KYC), for this you will be asked for a proof of address, ID and to verify your phone number, it's a matter of a few minutes. The documents sent will be processed within 24H maximum.

üî∏Effect a deposit on Binance:üî∏
1Ô∏è‚É£Start by funding your ADVcash wallet by going to the "Deposit Funds" section enter the amount you want as well as the currency and country that corresponds then, select the desired deposit method (SEPA) for example and click deposit, then follow the instructions given on the site.
The deadlines are 24/48h working hours to fund the account in SEPA.
2Ô∏è‚É£Go to Binance then, Wallet -> Deposit -> Fiat -> Advcash -> select the desired amount -> Confirm
3Ô∏è‚É£You will be redirected to the advcash site where you will need to confirm the deposit (you may be asked to verify via email).
4Ô∏è‚É£Your deposit is now available from your spot portfolio on Binance

üî∏Make a withdrawal from Binance üî∏
1Ô∏è‚É£Go to Binance then, Wallet -> Withdrawal -> Fiat -> Advcash -> select the amount you want -> Confirm
2Ô∏è‚É£Enter your Advcash account email address and then enter the requested 2FA information, your transfer to ADVcash will then be done instantly and without charge.
3Ô∏è‚É£If you want to send it to your bank go to "send funds" / To bank / SEPA and let the site guide you, a fee of 0.5% + 5‚Ç?will be applied.

Dear Binance,
We are the wind orchestra "G.Rossini" (Italy, Latina), born in 1952 and, for us, 2020 and 2021 have been very difficult. In addition to the Covid emergency that we are experiencing and has prevented us from making concerts, there has been the lack of a venue where we can rehearse, due to security issues, but, despite this, we have not lost heart. 
Our desire would be to organize concerts throughout the year both in our city and in the rest of the world, as we did before.
We are a group of 60 people, there are professionals, conservatory students and many young people who love music.

We have won several international competitions:

"21st International Festival Of Wind Orchetras Prague":
first prize with the score of 90,3/100 in the middle class category and the special prize for the best performance of the compulsory piece.

"XXI National Competition for Band La Bacchetta d'oro":
First prize with a score of 90,68/100 in the second category

XVIII Band Competition Riva Del Garda:
third place with a score of 90.13/100 competing for the first category.

XVII Riva Del Garda Band Competition:
first place with a score of 91,42/100 second category

XII Band Competition city of Scandicci:
first place

For this reason we are writing this letter to you, hoping that it will be accepted, in order to make our wish come true. It would also be great to collaborate with Binance, and we could compose (we have very good composers known in the world in our group) and record music for Binance!

I'll end this letter with some photos and a comment from the famous composer David Holsinger:

"WOW! This band is incredible. What a marvelous performance! I am very impressed with the flair of this group and their illustrious conductor! Well done!"

(www.instagram.com/orchestradifiatirossinilatina/)
(www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100028941266403)

To view the image of a Binance NFT owned on a non-Binance address:

- Go to the Binance NFT contract: https://bscscan.com/token/0xc014b45d680b5a4bf51ccda778a68d5251c14b5e
- Go to the Contract / Read the contract tab
- Go to "21. tokenURI" (bottom of page)
- Enter the "Token_id" of your NFT (visible in the list of your "Erc721 Token Txns" on bscscan for example)
- Click on "Request"
- Retrieve the "tokenURI" that was generated
- Keep only the characters after "ipfs://ipfs/"
- Access the URL "https://ipfs.io/ipfs/" followed by the characters kept
- You now have access to the name and URL of your NFT Binance image

Yes, as long as it is $10+ or it reaches the minimum trade threshold. (Futures trading might offer limited pairs)

I would say yes because you have a liquidation price, if the crypto reaches this price, your position is liquidated.
Using a higher leverage reduces the gap of this liquidation price, thus you are taking more risks
so i must chose a target price, an expiration date to trade futures ?
And if the trade hits the target price before expiration time i make money ?

You choose to long (expecting an increase) or short (expecting a decrease) a token with a custom leverage (x1 to x125 for some tokens)
If you long and the price is decreasing too much, you get liquidated, but if it follows your expectations you will win way more than a classic x1 spot trading
(I'm kinda new to futures so I may be wrong on some points, but that is what I saw so far)

Adam

For an OCO order you have these fields : (example)
Limit (the price where you want to take profit) : 56$
Stop (the trigger price for the spot limit) : 50$ 
Stop-limit (the price of your spot-limit order) : 49$
Amount (classic amount of tokens) : 100%

Here : I buy the token Y at 54$, if the prices reaches 56$ the limit is triggered and all my amount is sold at this price (56$), if the price decreases to 50$ my stop-limit is triggered : a new sell order at 49$ is created (and probably instantly done)
So if I understand right, the Stop has to be triggered first before the coin can be sold?
Thank you! You've been an incredible help btw!
yes, because if you create a sell order at 49$ and if the current price is at 60$, it will instantly be sold (and thats not what you want)
when I use stop limits I usually put the same price for the stop & stop-limit, so in my head its just "if it decreases to X, I sell"
That would've been my next question. Thank you for your help!
